.TH "HTMLCanvasElement.webglcontextrestored_event" "JS" "July 7, 2023" "JavaScript" "JavaScript Reference Manual"
.SH NAME
HTMLCanvasElement.webglcontextrestored_event \- HTMLCanvasElement:
webglcontextrestored event
.SH SYNOPSIS
The \f[B]\f[CB]webglcontextrestored\f[B]\f[R] event of the WebGL API is
fired if the user agent restores the drawing buffer for a
\f[CR]WebGLRenderingContext\f[R] object.
.PP
Once the context is restored, WebGL resources such as textures and
buffers that were created before the context was lost are no longer
valid.
You need to reinitialize the state of your WebGL application and
recreate resources.
.PP
This event does not bubble.
.SH SYNTAX
Use the event name in methods like \f[CR]addEventListener()\f[R], or set
an event handler property.
.IP
.EX
addEventListener(\[dq]webglcontextrestored\[dq], (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {});

onwebglcontextrestored = (event) \f[B]=>\f[R] {};
.EE
.SH EVENT TYPE
A \f[CR]WebGLContextEvent\f[R].
Inherits from \f[CR]Event\f[R].
.SH EVENT PROPERTIES
\f[I]This interface inherits properties from its parent interface,
\f[CI]Event\f[I].\f[R]
.TP
\f[B]WebGLContextEvent.statusMessage\f[R]
A read\-only property containing additional information about the event.
.SH EXAMPLE
With the help of the \f[CR]WEBGL_lose_context\f[R] extension, you can
simulate the \f[CR]webglcontextrestored\f[R] event:
.IP
.EX
\f[B]const\f[R] canvas = document.getElementById(\[dq]canvas\[dq]);
\f[B]const\f[R] gl = canvas.getContext(\[dq]webgl\[dq]);

canvas.addEventListener(
  \[dq]webglcontextrestored\[dq],
  (e) \f[B]=>\f[R] {
    console.log(e);
  },
  \f[B]false\f[R],
);

gl.getExtension(\[dq]WEBGL_lose_context\[dq]).restoreContext();

\f[I]// \[dq]webglcontextrestored\[dq] event is logged.\f[R]
.EE
